        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: introduce pond (peer discovery + bridge + ssh-mesh)",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Adds `--pond NAME` flag + reserved `pond=` provider label. A pond is a small group of crabbox leases that share a private network, peer name resolution, and lifecycle. Single-box use is a pond of one; existing flows unchanged.\n- Three transport planes:\n  - **Tailscale** — managed Linux (Hetzner / Azure / GCP) peer mesh via ACL tag + cloud-init systemd timer rewriting `/etc/hosts.cbx`. Stable hostnames `<slug>.cbx`.\n  - **Bridge** — delegated URL providers (Islo / E2B / Railway) expose HTTPS endpoints via the new `BridgeProvider` interface.\n  - **SSH-mesh** — SSH-only providers get operator-side `ssh -L` via `crabbox pond connect --export`.\n- `crabbox doctor --pond NAME` reports cross-plane reachability.\n- Worker reserves the `pond` label key. Broker never holds Tailscale credentials.\n- Folds in the bridge plane (#136) and SSH-mesh (#137) — one PR, one review thread.\n\n## Naming\nRenamed `crew` → `pond` to align with the crab-biology aesthetic already used across openclaw (crabbox, crabyard, crabpot). `pool` is taken (warm-lease pool in `pool.go`). A pond is a small contained body where a few connected creatures live — same shape as this feature.\n\n## Verification\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `cd worker && pnpm test && pnpm typecheck`\n- `crabbox doctor --pond smoke` against a real Hetzner pond\n\n## Live smoke\n```\n$ crabbox warmup --pond it-$SHA --slug api --provider hetzner --tailscale\n$ crabbox warmup --pond it-$SHA --slug ml  --provider modal   --class a10g\n$ crabbox warmup --pond it-$SHA --slug db  --provider hetzner --tailscale\n$ crabbox run --id it-$SHA-api -- \"ML_HOST=ml.cbx DB_HOST=db.cbx go test ./...\"\nPASS\nok  example.com/svc  31.4s\n$ crabbox release --pond it-$SHA\n```\n\n## Codex findings — all resolved\n- `pool.go` coordinator-path label drop → `CoordinatorLease.Pond` added + propagated in `leaseToServerTarget`.\n- `pool.go` typed-slice filter → JSON round-trip in `filterJSONListViewByPond`.\n- `doctor_pond.go` substring-match → per-rule structural acls/grants parse.\n- `lease_flags.go` bootstrap-on-reuse → guarded on `existingLeaseID == \"\"`.\n- `pond_acl.go` hujson decode (handles `//` comments in real policies).\n- Owner segment switched from 7-char truncate to stable `base32(sha256(email))[:7]` hash.\n- Hetzner provisioner now populates `TailscaleIPv4` on the claim sidecar (Bridge plane works on merge instead of permanent `transport=pending`).\n\n## Deferred (follow-up PRs)\n- Modal / Cloudflare / Tensorlake bridge adapters.\n- macOS / Windows plane.\n- `crabbox pond gc` for stale Tailscale tag cleanup.\n- Pond cost aggregation.\n- `--isolation per-slug` mode.\n\n## API stability\n`pond` is **preview** for v0.x. The reserved label key stays; the flag shape may evolve. Stable from v1.0.\n",
